 J</em> 2008;14(2):153–157.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1524-4741.2007.00546.x">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18248562/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+multi-site+validation+trial+of+radioactive+seed+localization+as+an+alternative+to+wire+localization&amp;author=JH+Hughes&amp;author=MC+Mason&amp;author=RJ+Gray&amp;publication_year=2008&amp;journal=Breast+J&amp;pages=153-157&amp;doi=10.1111%2Fj.1524-4741.2007.00546.x&amp;pmid=18248562">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">30.</div><div id="r30" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Lovrics PJ, Goldsmith CH, Hodgson N, et al. A multicentered, randomized, controlled trial comparing radioguided seed localization to standard wire localization for nonpalpable, invasive and in situ breast carcinomas. <em>Ann Surg Oncol</em> 2011;18(12):3407–3414.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1245/s10434-011-1699-y">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21533657/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+multicentered%2C+randomized%2C+controlled+trial+comparing+radioguided+seed+localization+to+standard+wire+localization+for+nonpalpable%2C+invasive+and+in+situ+breast+carcinomas&amp;author=PJ+Lovrics&amp;author=CH+Goldsmith&amp;author=N+Hodgson&amp;publication_year=2011&amp;journal=Ann+Surg+Oncol&amp;pages=3407-3414&amp;doi=10.1245%2Fs10434-011-1699-y&amp;pmid=21533657">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">31.</div><div id="r31" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class=